headline: EL Q4 Deep Dive: Market Reacts to Margin Shortfall Despite Revenue Growth
summary: Beauty products company Estée Lauder (NYSE:EL) met Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q4 CY2025, with sales up 5.6% year on year to $4.23 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.89 per share was 6.6% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
